* -c|--check switch, instead of null: null imput -> help

* implement the ability to specify remote host by IP (actual), by local name
 (via /etc/hosts) or by FQDN (via internet/DNS):
    RHOST_RESOLV=IP|LNAME|FQDN

    IP: standard IPv4 w.x.y.z
    LNAME: the last part of /etc/host entry
    FQDN: fully qualified domain name (without protocol prefix: www.sample.com,
         not http://www.sample.com/)

* debian package
